Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:19.34,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,It began here at the Kennedy Space Center Florida last summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:19.34,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,这一切开始于去年夏天的佛罗里达州肯尼迪航天中心
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.86,0:00:25.24,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,A pair of spacecraft Viking 1 and Viking 2 were readied for their separate journeys to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.86,0:00:25.24,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,那时 海盗1号和海盗2号航天器已经准备好分别前往火星
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.48,0:00:28.80,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Each is really two spacecraft in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.48,0:00:28.80,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,(实际上) 海盗号的每个航天器都由两个航天器组成
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.22,0:00:32.69,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,A 5,000 pound orbiter with cameras and communications gear
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.22,0:00:32.69,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,一个带有相机和通讯设备 重达2.268吨的轨道器
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.93,0:00:37.79,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,and sealed inside to saucer-like capsules at the other end, the Viking landing craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.93,0:00:37.79,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,并将其封盖在另一端的碟状舱 海盗号着陆舱外
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.31,0:00:43.06,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,A camera equipped automated biological and chemistry laboratory and seismic station
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.31,0:00:43.06,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,着陆舱上装有相机 自动化生物和化学实验室 以及地震台
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.32,0:00:47.36,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,which has been purged of Earthly organisms by being heated in a huge oven.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.32,0:00:47.36,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,而通过在一个巨大的炉子里加热的方法 已经清除了这些航天器上携带的地球生物
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:56.34,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,The 11-month, 420-million-mile trip for the two Viking orbiter Landers was set in motion by two launches.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:56.34,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,通过两次对两艘海盗号轨道器和着陆器的发射 将启动为期11个月 6.8亿公里的行程
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.60,0:01:00.67,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,One in August. One in September.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.60,0:01:00.67,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,两次发射分别发生在8月和9月
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.81,0:01:07.90,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Earth shrinks smaller and smaller as the two Vikings head toward their Martian rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.81,0:01:07.90,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,当两艘海盗号在与火星交会时 其视野内的地球将越变越小
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.73,0:01:11.50,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Then, braking rockets fire on command,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.73,0:01:11.50,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,(在交会时) 制动火箭将按指令点火
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.56,0:01:16.30,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,slowing the first Viking Explorer enough that it goes into orbit around Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.56,0:01:16.30,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,减慢第一艘海盗号探测器的速度 使其足以进入绕火轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.58,0:01:21.97,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,For the next two weeks, the orbiting spacecraft will survey the surface below,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.58,0:01:21.97,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,在开始绕火的两周内 轨道器将勘测下方的火星地表
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:26.38,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,transmitting pictures of possible landing sites to scientists on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:26.38,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,向地球上的科学家发送可能的着陆地点的照片
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.95,0:01:32.32,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,The Martian surface should be a study in contrasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.95,0:01:32.32,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,对火星表面的研究会涉及到对比
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.81,0:01:38.19,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,From vast dust swept plains to immense canyons and frost covered plateaus,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.81,0:01:38.19,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,火星的地形 既有尘土飞扬的广阔平原 也有巨大的峡谷和覆盖着冰霜的高原
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.75,0:01:43.01,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,huge gullies and channels photographed by earlier Mariner spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.75,0:01:43.01,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,还有纵横的沟壑 这些都被之前的水手号航天器拍摄到了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.03,0:01:47.28,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,are believed to have been caused by running water sometime in the distant past.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.03,0:01:47.28,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,据信是由远古时期的流水造成的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.42,0:01:51.75,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,If all goes as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.42,0:01:51.75,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,如果一切按计划进行
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.02,0:01:57.67,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,the first Viking Lander will separate from the orbiting command ship and descend to the Martian surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.02,0:01:57.67,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,第一艘海盗号着陆器将与轨道(指令)器分离 并下降到火星表面
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.02,0:02:02.07,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Landing at 9:40 p.m. Eastern Daylight Time July 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.02,0:02:02.07,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,在美国东部夏令时间7月4日晚上9点40分着陆
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.86,0:02:09.75,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,The second Viking is scheduled to land on September 4th, 1000 miles to the northeast of Viking 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.86,0:02:09.75,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,第二艘海盗号计划于9月4日 在海盗1号东北方向1609公里处着陆
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.76,0:02:13.93,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,How will Viking go about looking for life on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.76,0:02:13.93,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,那么 海盗号将如何去寻找火星上的生命呢
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.39,0:02:18.29,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,We asked Dr. Richard Young, NASA's chief of planetary biology.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.39,0:02:18.29,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,我们请教了NASA的行星生物学主管 理查德·杨博士
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.99,0:02:23.36,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,We look for life on Mars in much the same way we would look for life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.99,0:02:23.36,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,我们在火星和在地球上寻找生命的方式是差不多的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:28.53,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,if we were forced to use an automated device and we don't send a scientist along
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:28.53,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,如果我们被迫使用自动装置且不派科学家一起去找的话
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:31.88,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,if we were sending a little wagon out into the Sahara Desert
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:31.88,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,如果我们派一辆小马车到撒哈拉沙漠去的话
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.93,0:02:34.10,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,or one of the dry valleys of the Antarctic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.93,0:02:34.10,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,或者是一段干燥的南极山谷
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:38.62,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,which had to function all by itself with automated equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:38.62,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,同时 这台设备还必须用自动化设备进行运作
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:40.65,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,this is probably exactly what we would sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:40.65,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,而这很可能就和我们要做的一样
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.40,0:02:44.89,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,And let me say by the way that we're looking primarily for microorganisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.40,0:02:44.89,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,让我顺便说一下 我们主要是在寻找微生物
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:49.98,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,It would be rather fruitless of us for to look for horses on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:49.98,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,(因为)我们在火星上找马的话可能是徒劳的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.49,0:02:53.01,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't look for horses on Earth if we were looking for life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.49,0:02:53.01,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,就算是在地球上寻找生命 也不可能(一开始)就找马(这种大型生物)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.05,0:02:58.03,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,because the chances would be median to one against finding them with a random search.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.05,0:02:58.03,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,因为随便找找 就能找到的几率不高
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:03.40,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Vikings mechanical arm pulls in a scoop full of Martian soil
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:03.40,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,海盗人的机械臂取出了满满一瓢火星土壤
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:05.94,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,and drops it into a one cubic foot box.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:05.94,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,然后把火星土壤扔进一个30升的盒子里
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.99,0:03:09.45,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,That's really three completely automated testing laboratories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.99,0:03:09.45,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,这实际上是三个完全自动化的检测实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:15.14,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,It is here that the possibilities for or against the presence of life will be determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:15.14,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,在这里 生命存在与否的可能性将被确定
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.32,0:03:22.77,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,What will it mean to Earthlings if life is found on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.32,0:03:22.77,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,那么 如果在火星上发现生命 对地球人意味着什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:29.96,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,It must mean that the universe is literally an inhabited universe with many planets that have life on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:29.96,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,这一定意味着宇宙是一个有别的生命存在的宇宙 其中许多星球上都有生命
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.88,0:03:32.87,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Now if there are many planets that have life on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.88,0:03:32.87,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,那么如果有许多星球上有生命
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:34.99,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,there is no doubt at all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:34.99,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,毋庸置疑
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.48,0:03:43.08,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,that terrestrial life is not going to be the most advanced civilization, the most highest level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.48,0:03:43.08,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,地球上的生命(可能)不会是最先进的文明 不具有最高层次的意识
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:46.80,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,We must be somewheres in the broad spectrum of possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:46.80,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,我们肯定是在广泛的(存在生命的)可能性范围内的某个位置上
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:49.06,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,And that drives you to the conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:49.06,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,这让你得出了一个结论
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:54.83,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,is that there may be conscious life elsewhere in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:54.83,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,那么就是宇宙中其他的地方 可能存在有意识的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.50,0:04:00.55,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,Vikings to Mars and the search for life there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.50,0:04:00.55,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,海盗号来到火星 并在那里寻找生命
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.75,0:04:04.94,720P-sgbd-27,,0,0,0,,This country's first close-up scientific exploration of the Red Planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.75,0:04:04.94,720P-sgsm-42,,0,0,0,,这是这个国家对红色星球的第一次近距离科学探索
